.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-1-4::.
City: rome, liverpool, colone, berlin, london, hamburg
The people use 6 different means of transport: airplane, bike, helicopter, ship, snowmobile, taxi
1. the person driving the airplane is on the far left##1
2. the person traveling to colone is on the far left##1
3. the person driving the snowmobile is on the right of the person driving the taxi##1
4. the person traveling to hamburg is on the left of the person traveling to london##1
5. the person driving the taxi is the person traveling to berlin##1
6. the person driving the bike is on the right of the person driving the ship##1
7. the person traveling to london is on the far right##1
8. the person driving the helicopter is on the right of the person traveling to rome##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |   2   |     3      |     4      |   5   |    6    |
| City   | colone  | berlin | rome      | liverpool  | hamburg | london |
| Transport     | airplane | taxi  | snowmobile | helicopter | ship  | bike    |

